main event: A housewife observed twelve to fifteen round, silver-colored objects at a high altitude in 3 Sept 1947, Oswego, Oregon. No further information was submitted, therefore, no conclusion can be reached.
interesting points: The observation occurred in Oswego, Oregon, with only one witness present, despite the presence of a plane in the sky at that time.
The report mentions other incidents in the same locality involving groups of unidentified round or discoid objects.
The document contains Dr. Hynek's evaluations extracted from Project Grudge report, categorizing incidents based on probabilities and possible explanations.
The text also mentions the psychological explanations for the unidentified flying objects, attributing errors in identification to an inability to estimate speed, distance, and size.
The UFO checklist for Incident #61 describes a 17-18 ft round silver object seen in flight in Omegon, Oregon on 5 Sept 1947 at 1215 hours.
